(\int_{X} |f+g|^p d\mu)^{\frac{1}{p}} \le (\int_{X} |f|^p d\mu)^{\frac{1}{p}} d\mu +(\int_{X} |g|^p)^{\frac{1}{p}} d\mu)
A=(\int_{X} |f|^p d\mu)^{\frac{1}{p}}
B=(\int_{X} |g|^p)^{\frac{1}{p}} d\mu
f_1=\frac{f}{A}
g_1=\frac{g}{B}
\int_{X} (Af_1+Bg_1)^p d\mu \le (A+B)^p
\int_{X} (\frac{Af_1+Bg_1}{A+B})^p d\mu \le 1
\int_{X} (\frac{Af_1+Bg_1}{A+B})^p d\mu \le \int_{X} \frac{A|f_1|^p+B|g_1|^p}{A+B} d\mu
